  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether treatment with valganciclovir decreases T
      cell activation levels among HIV-infected patients with asymptomatic cytomegalovirus (CMV)
      co-infection, potentially improving immune responses to antiretroviral therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
